INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A solutions architect is designing a multi-tier web application on a public cloud platform. The application must remain available even if a single data center experiences a complete outage. The architect decides to distribute workloads across multiple locations within the same geographic region. Which cloud concept BEST describes the infrastructure strategy being used?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Multi-region deployment"},{"id":"b","text":"Availability zone redundancy"},{"id":"c","text":"Content delivery network (CDN) caching"},{"id":"d","text":"Vertical scaling (scale-up)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Availability zones (AZs) are physically separate data centers within the same geographic region, each with independent power, cooling, and networking. Distributing workloads across multiple AZs protects against a single data-center failure while keeping latency low. Multi-region deployment (a) spans geographically distant regions, which is more than what the scenario describes. A CDN (c) accelerates content delivery but does not provide compute redundancy. Vertical scaling (d) increases the size of a single instance and does nothing for fault tolerance.$patch$, $patch$Cloud Architecture and Design$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/training/resources/exam-objectives/comptia-cloud-cv0-004-exam-objectives","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives – Domain 1: Cloud Architecture and Design"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/using-regions-availability-zones.html","label":"AWS – Regions and Availability Zones"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A solutions architect is designing a multi-tier web application on a public cloud platform. The application must remain available even if a single data center experiences a complete outage. The architect decides to distribute workloads across multiple locations within the same geographic region. Which cloud concept BEST describes the infrastructure strategy being used?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud architect is evaluating service models for a new internal analytics platform. The development team wants full control over the operating system, middleware, and runtime environment, but does not want to manage physical hardware or the hypervisor layer. Which cloud service model BEST satisfies these requirements?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Software as a Service (SaaS)"},{"id":"b","text":"Function as a Service (FaaS)"},{"id":"c","text":"Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS)"},{"id":"d","text":"Platform as a Service (PaaS)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$IaaS provides virtualized compute, storage, and networking resources while abstracting the underlying physical hardware and hypervisor. This gives the team full control over the OS, middleware, and runtime, satisfying the requirement. SaaS (a) delivers fully managed applications with no control over the underlying stack. FaaS (b) abstracts away the OS and runtime entirely, exposing only event-driven function execution. PaaS (d) manages the OS and runtime on behalf of the consumer, limiting low-level control that the team requires.$patch$, $patch$Cloud Architecture and Design$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/training/resources/exam-objectives/comptia-cloud-cv0-004-exam-objectives","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives – Domain 1: Cloud Architecture and Design"},{"url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/Legacy/SP/nistspecialpublication800-145.pdf","label":"NIST SP 800-145 – The NIST Definition of Cloud Computing"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud architect is evaluating service models for a new internal analytics platform. The development team wants full control over the operating system, middleware, and runtime environment, but does not want to manage physical hardware or the hypervisor layer. Which cloud service model BEST satisfies these requirements?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An organization is architecting a cloud environment and must choose a deployment model. The requirements are: sensitive workloads must remain on infrastructure exclusively controlled by the organization, while less sensitive workloads can leverage shared public cloud resources to reduce cost. Which deployment model BEST meets these requirements?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Community cloud"},{"id":"b","text":"Public cloud only"},{"id":"c","text":"Hybrid cloud"},{"id":"d","text":"Private cloud only"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A hybrid cloud combines a private cloud (or on-premises infrastructure) with one or more public cloud environments, connected in a way that allows data and applications to be shared between them. This model lets the organization keep sensitive workloads on exclusively controlled infrastructure while offloading less sensitive workloads to the cost-effective public cloud. A community cloud (a) is shared among organizations with common concerns but does not provide exclusive organizational control. A public cloud only (b) does not satisfy the exclusivity requirement for sensitive data. A private cloud only (d) satisfies security requirements but forfeits the cost benefits of public cloud for less sensitive workloads.$patch$, $patch$Cloud Architecture and Design$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/training/resources/exam-objectives/comptia-cloud-cv0-004-exam-objectives","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives – Domain 1: Cloud Architecture and Design"},{"url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/Legacy/SP/nistspecialpublication800-145.pdf","label":"NIST SP 800-145 – The NIST Definition of Cloud Computing (Deployment Models)"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An organization is architecting a cloud environment and must choose a deployment model. The requirements are: sensitive workloads must remain on infrastructure exclusively controlled by the organization, while less sensitive workloads can leverage shared public cloud resources to reduce cost. Which deployment model BEST meets these requirements?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud engineer is deploying a web application that must automatically add or remove virtual machine instances based on CPU utilization thresholds. Which deployment feature should be configured to achieve this behavior?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Load balancer health checks"},{"id":"b","text":"Auto scaling groups with scaling policies"},{"id":"c","text":"Reserved instance scheduling"},{"id":"d","text":"Elastic IP address allocation"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Auto scaling groups with scaling policies allow the cloud platform to automatically increase or decrease the number of compute instances based on defined metrics such as CPU utilization. Load balancer health checks monitor instance availability but do not add or remove instances. Reserved instance scheduling is a billing/purchasing model, not a dynamic scaling feature. Elastic IP addresses provide static public IPs and have no relation to capacity scaling.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/auto-scaling-groups.html","label":"AWS Auto Scaling Groups Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud engineer is deploying a web application that must automatically add or remove virtual machine instances based on CPU utilization thresholds. Which deployment feature should be configured to achieve this behavior?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$During a cloud deployment, a DevOps team wants to ensure that infrastructure is defined and managed through code files stored in version control rather than through manual console changes. Which practice does this describe?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Continuous integration"},{"id":"b","text":"Infrastructure as Code (IaC)"},{"id":"c","text":"Blue/green deployment"},{"id":"d","text":"Configuration drift remediation"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Infrastructure as Code (IaC) is the practice of defining and provisioning cloud infrastructure using declarative or imperative code files (e.g., Terraform, CloudFormation, ARM templates) stored in version control. Continuous integration refers to the automated building and testing of application code. Blue/green deployment is a release strategy that uses two identical environments to reduce downtime. Configuration drift remediation addresses unintended changes to existing resources but is not the overall practice of defining infrastructure as code.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/devops/deliver/what-is-infrastructure-as-code","label":"Microsoft Azure: What is Infrastructure as Code?"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/Welcome.html","label":"AWS CloudFormation User Guide"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$During a cloud deployment, a DevOps team wants to ensure that infrastructure is defined and managed through code files stored in version control rather than through manual console changes. Which practice does this describe?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A company is deploying a containerized microservices application to the cloud. The operations team needs a platform that will automatically handle container scheduling, self-healing, and service discovery. Which technology best meets these requirements?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Docker Compose"},{"id":"b","text":"A bare-metal hypervisor"},{"id":"c","text":"A container orchestration platform such as Kubernetes"},{"id":"d","text":"An object storage bucket"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Kubernetes and similar container orchestration platforms provide automated container scheduling, self-healing (restarting failed containers), and built-in service discovery. Docker Compose is designed for single-host, multi-container applications and lacks the cluster-level orchestration features required. A bare-metal hypervisor manages virtual machines, not containers, and does not provide these features natively. Object storage buckets are used for storing unstructured data and are unrelated to container workload management.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/","label":"Kubernetes Official Documentation – Overview"},{"url":"https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/concepts/kubernetes-engine-overview","label":"Google Kubernetes Engine Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A company is deploying a containerized microservices application to the cloud. The operations team needs a platform that will automatically handle container scheduling, self-healing, and service discovery. Which technology best meets these requirements?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An organization is deploying a new application version and wants to minimize risk by running both the old version (v1) and new version (v2) simultaneously, shifting traffic gradually from v1 to v2. Which deployment strategy is being used?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Recreate deployment"},{"id":"b","text":"Canary deployment"},{"id":"c","text":"Rolling deployment"},{"id":"d","text":"A/B testing deployment"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A canary deployment releases a new version to a small subset of users or servers first, then gradually increases traffic to the new version while monitoring for errors, minimizing risk. A recreate deployment terminates all old instances before starting new ones, causing downtime. A rolling deployment replaces instances incrementally but does not specifically route a controlled percentage of traffic by design. A/B testing is used to compare two variants for user behavior experiments, not primarily for risk-managed production releases.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://cloud.google.com/architecture/application-deployment-and-testing-strategies","label":"Google Cloud: Deployment Strategies"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/codedeploy/latest/userguide/deployment-configurations.html","label":"AWS CodeDeploy Deployment Configurations"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An organization is deploying a new application version and wants to minimize risk by running both the old version (v1) and new version (v2) simultaneously, shifting traffic gradually from v1 to v2. Which deployment strategy is being used?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud architect is designing a deployment for a stateless web application that must serve users across three geographic regions. The architect wants requests routed to the closest healthy region. Which cloud service should be implemented?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"A single-region application load balancer"},{"id":"b","text":"A global DNS-based load balancer with latency routing"},{"id":"c","text":"A content delivery network origin shield"},{"id":"d","text":"A site-to-site VPN gateway"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A global DNS-based load balancer with latency routing directs client requests to the closest healthy regional endpoint, satisfying both the geographic distribution and health-check requirements. A single-region application load balancer operates within one region and cannot route between regions. A CDN origin shield reduces load on origins but does not route application traffic to healthy regional deployments. A site-to-site VPN gateway provides encrypted connectivity between networks and does not perform application-layer traffic routing.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/Route53/latest/DeveloperGuide/routing-policy-latency.html","label":"AWS Route 53 Latency-Based Routing"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/traffic-manager/traffic-manager-overview","label":"Azure Traffic Manager Overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud architect is designing a deployment for a stateless web application that must serve users across three geographic regions. The architect wants requests routed to the closest healthy region. Which cloud service should be implemented?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A team is using a CI/CD pipeline to deploy application updates. After a deployment, the pipeline must automatically test the new environment and, if tests fail, restore the previous known-good state without manual intervention. Which capability satisfies this requirement?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Automated rollback triggered by failed pipeline tests"},{"id":"b","text":"Manual snapshot restoration by an administrator"},{"id":"c","text":"Reserved capacity pre-warming"},{"id":"d","text":"Resource tagging policies"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Automated rollback in a CI/CD pipeline uses post-deployment test results as a gate; if tests fail, the pipeline automatically reverts to the prior deployment artifact or infrastructure state without human intervention. Manual snapshot restoration requires administrator action, violating the 'no manual intervention' requirement. Reserved capacity pre-warming improves startup performance but does not address failed deployments. Resource tagging policies apply governance metadata and have no bearing on deployment rollback.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/codepipeline/latest/userguide/actions-invoke-lambda-function.html","label":"AWS CodePipeline – Automatic Rollback"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/devops/pipelines/release/define-multistage-release-process","label":"Azure Pipelines – Rollback Strategies"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A team is using a CI/CD pipeline to deploy application updates. After a deployment, the pipeline must automatically test the new environment and, if tests fail, restore the previous known-good state without manual intervention. Which capability satisfies this requirement?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A company wants to deploy workloads that require direct access to underlying physical hardware for licensing and performance reasons, while still using a cloud provider's data center. Which cloud deployment model should the company select?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Shared public cloud tenancy"},{"id":"b","text":"Dedicated (bare-metal) instances"},{"id":"c","text":"Serverless function deployment"},{"id":"d","text":"Platform as a Service (PaaS) hosting"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Dedicated or bare-metal instances provide a single-tenant physical server hosted in the cloud provider's data center, giving the customer direct access to the hardware without a hypervisor layer. This satisfies hardware-licensing requirements (e.g., per-socket or per-core licenses) and maximum performance needs. Shared public cloud tenancy uses multi-tenant virtualized resources, preventing direct hardware access. Serverless functions abstract all infrastructure away from the user. PaaS offerings also abstract the underlying OS and hardware, making them unsuitable for workloads requiring direct hardware access.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/dedicated-hosts-overview.html","label":"AWS EC2 Dedicated Hosts Documentation"},{"url":"https://www.ibm.com/cloud/bare-metal-servers","label":"IBM Cloud Bare Metal Servers Overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A company wants to deploy workloads that require direct access to underlying physical hardware for licensing and performance reasons, while still using a cloud provider's data center. Which cloud deployment model should the company select?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An engineer is deploying a cloud-native application and must ensure that secrets such as database passwords and API keys are not hardcoded in configuration files or environment variables visible in deployment manifests. Which solution best addresses this requirement?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Store secrets in a dedicated secrets management service and inject them at runtime"},{"id":"b","text":"Base64-encode the secrets and embed them in the source code repository"},{"id":"c","text":"Include secrets in the container image layers"},{"id":"d","text":"Pass secrets as plaintext query strings in the application URL"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A dedicated secrets management service (e.g., AWS Secrets Manager, Azure Key Vault, HashiCorp Vault) stores credentials encrypted at rest and injects them into applications at runtime via API calls or sidecar patterns, eliminating plaintext exposure in manifests or code. Base64-encoding provides no security; secrets remain trivially recoverable and should never be committed to source control. Embedding secrets in container image layers bakes them into a distributable artifact, creating a significant security risk. Passing secrets as plaintext query strings exposes them in server logs, browser history, and network traffic.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/secretsmanager/latest/userguide/intro.html","label":"AWS Secrets Manager Documentation"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/key-vault/general/overview","label":"Azure Key Vault Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An engineer is deploying a cloud-native application and must ensure that secrets such as database passwords and API keys are not hardcoded in configuration files or environment variables visible in deployment manifests. Which solution best addresses this requirement?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A SaaS provider needs to deploy a new feature to production with zero downtime. They maintain two identical production environments (Blue and Green). After deploying and validating the new release on the Green environment, what is the correct next step in a blue/green deployment?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Shut down the Blue environment immediately before switching traffic"},{"id":"b","text":"Switch the load balancer or DNS to route all traffic to the Green environment"},{"id":"c","text":"Deploy the same release to the Blue environment simultaneously with Green"},{"id":"d","text":"Delete all resources in the Green environment after validation"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$In a blue/green deployment, once the new version is validated on the Green environment, traffic is shifted by updating the load balancer or DNS record to point to Green. The Blue environment remains intact and idle, serving as an instant rollback target if problems emerge. Shutting down Blue before switching would eliminate the rollback option and could cause downtime. Deploying the same release to both environments simultaneously defeats the purpose of the pattern. Deleting Green after validation is the opposite of what should happen—Blue would eventually be decommissioned or repurposed, not Green.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/whitepapers/latest/overview-deployment-options/bluegreen-deployments.html","label":"AWS Blue/Green Deployments"},{"url":"https://cloud.google.com/architecture/application-deployment-and-testing-strategies#blue-green_deployment_strategy","label":"Google Cloud: Blue-Green Deployment Strategy"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A SaaS provider needs to deploy a new feature to production with zero downtime. They maintain two identical production environments (Blue and Green). After deploying and validating the new release on the Green environment, what is the correct next step in a blue/green deployment?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud engineer is deploying virtual machines using an ARM template and notices that some resources are being created before their dependencies are ready, causing deployment failures. Which ARM template feature should the engineer use to enforce resource creation order?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The 'copy' loop element"},{"id":"b","text":"The 'dependsOn' property"},{"id":"c","text":"The 'condition' property"},{"id":"d","text":"The 'outputs' section"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The 'dependsOn' property in an ARM template explicitly declares that one resource must be fully provisioned before another resource begins deploying, enforcing a creation order. The 'copy' loop element is used to deploy multiple instances of a resource but does not control inter-resource ordering. The 'condition' property controls whether a resource is deployed at all based on a Boolean expression, not the order of deployment. The 'outputs' section returns values after deployment completes and has no effect on resource creation sequencing.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-resource-manager/templates/define-resource-dependency","label":"Microsoft Learn: Define the order for deploying resources in ARM templates"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud engineer is deploying virtual machines using an ARM template and notices that some resources are being created before their dependencies are ready, causing deployment failures. Which ARM template feature should the engineer use to enforce resource creation order?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud operations team wants to enforce that all new cloud resources deployed within the organization comply with corporate tagging standards and approved SKU sizes, and that non-compliant resources are automatically prevented from being created. Which cloud governance feature should be implemented?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Cloud cost anomaly detection alerts"},{"id":"b","text":"Cloud policy enforcement (e.g., Azure Policy or AWS Service Control Policies)"},{"id":"c","text":"Resource group RBAC role assignments"},{"id":"d","text":"Network security group rules"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Cloud policy enforcement tools such as Azure Policy or AWS Service Control Policies (SCPs) allow administrators to define rules that prevent non-compliant resources from being deployed (deny effect) and can audit or auto-remediate existing resources. Cost anomaly detection alerts notify teams of unexpected spending but cannot prevent resource creation. RBAC role assignments control who can perform actions but cannot enforce tagging standards or SKU restrictions at a policy level across all principals. Network security group rules govern inbound and outbound network traffic and are unrelated to resource compliance enforcement.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/governance/policy/overview","label":"Azure Policy Documentation"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/organizations/latest/userguide/orgs_manage_policies_scps.html","label":"AWS Service Control Policies Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud operations team wants to enforce that all new cloud resources deployed within the organization comply with corporate tagging standards and approved SKU sizes, and that non-compliant resources are automatically prevented from being created. Which cloud governance feature should be implemented?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A development team is deploying a microservices application and wants to ensure that each service can discover and communicate with other services dynamically without hardcoding IP addresses. Which cloud deployment component provides this capability?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"A static NAT gateway"},{"id":"b","text":"A service mesh with built-in service discovery (e.g., Istio, AWS App Mesh)"},{"id":"c","text":"A dedicated VPN concentrator"},{"id":"d","text":"A read replica database cluster"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A service mesh such as Istio or AWS App Mesh provides service discovery by maintaining a registry of service endpoints and proxying inter-service communication, allowing microservices to locate one another dynamically without relying on static IP addresses. A static NAT gateway translates private IP addresses for outbound internet traffic but does not provide service discovery. A VPN concentrator provides encrypted site-to-site or client-to-site connectivity and has no service registry or discovery function. A read replica database cluster is used for read-scaling of database workloads and is unrelated to microservice communication or discovery.$patch$, $patch$Deployment$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://istio.io/latest/docs/concepts/what-is-istio/","label":"Istio Service Mesh Documentation"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/app-mesh/latest/userguide/what-is-app-mesh.html","label":"AWS App Mesh Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A development team is deploying a microservices application and wants to ensure that each service can discover and communicate with other services dynamically without hardcoding IP addresses. Which cloud deployment component provides this capability?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud operations team receives alerts that a production workload's auto-scaling group has been launching new instances continuously for the past 20 minutes without stabilizing. CPU utilization across all instances remains below 10%. Which root cause is MOST likely responsible for this behavior?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The scale-out cooldown period is set too high, causing overlapping scale events."},{"id":"b","text":"A misconfigured health check is marking healthy instances as unhealthy, triggering continuous replacement."},{"id":"c","text":"The minimum instance count in the auto-scaling policy is set higher than the maximum instance count."},{"id":"d","text":"The cloud provider's compute quota for the region has been reached, throttling new launches."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$When CPU utilization is low yet instances keep launching, a scaling threshold breach is not the cause. A misconfigured health check (e.g., an HTTP health check pointing to a wrong path returning 500) will mark all newly launched instances as unhealthy, causing the auto-scaler to terminate and replace them in an endless loop. Option A is incorrect because a high cooldown would slow launches, not accelerate them. Option C is a configuration validation error that most platforms prevent or cap at the minimum. Option D would result in launch failures/errors, not a continuous launch loop.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/ec2-auto-scaling-health-checks.html","label":"AWS Auto Scaling Health Checks"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud operations team receives alerts that a production workload's auto-scaling group has been launching new instances continuously for the past 20 minutes without stabilizing. CPU utilization across all instances remains below 10%. Which root cause is MOST likely responsible for this behavior?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An operations engineer needs to ensure that all changes made to cloud infrastructure are traceable, reversible, and peer-reviewed before being applied to production. Which practice BEST satisfies all three requirements simultaneously?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Enabling cloud provider audit logging and sending logs to a SIEM."},{"id":"b","text":"Storing all infrastructure definitions as code in a version-controlled repository with mandatory pull-request approvals and automated rollback pipelines."},{"id":"c","text":"Scheduling weekly change-advisory board (CAB) meetings to review all proposed modifications."},{"id":"d","text":"Using a CMDB to document every infrastructure component and its owner."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Infrastructure as Code (IaC) stored in a version-controlled repository with pull-request gating provides traceability (commit history), peer review (PR approvals), and reversibility (rollback via previous commit or automated pipeline). Audit logging (A) provides traceability but not reversibility or pre-change review. CAB meetings (C) address review but not automated traceability or reversibility. A CMDB (D) documents state but does not inherently enforce review or rollback.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/devops/deliver/what-is-infrastructure-as-code","label":"Azure DevOps – Infrastructure as Code"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An operations engineer needs to ensure that all changes made to cloud infrastructure are traceable, reversible, and peer-reviewed before being applied to production. Which practice BEST satisfies all three requirements simultaneously?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A SaaS company operates a multi-tenant cloud application and has an SLA guaranteeing 99.9% monthly uptime to customers. During a post-incident review, the team calculates that 47 minutes of unplanned downtime occurred last month. Which conclusion is CORRECT?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The SLA was met because 47 minutes is within the 99.9% allowance of approximately 43.8 minutes per month."},{"id":"b","text":"The SLA was breached because 99.9% monthly uptime permits a maximum of approximately 43.8 minutes of downtime."},{"id":"c","text":"The SLA was met because 47 minutes represents less than 0.1% of a 30-day month."},{"id":"d","text":"The SLA was breached because any unplanned downtime automatically violates a 99.9% uptime commitment."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A 99.9% uptime SLA permits 0.1% downtime per month. In a 30-day month (43,200 minutes), 0.1% equals 43.2 minutes. 47 minutes exceeds this threshold, so the SLA is breached. Option A is incorrect because 47 minutes does exceed the ~43.2-minute allowance. Option C is incorrect; 47/43,200 ≈ 0.109%, which is above the 0.1% tolerance. Option D is incorrect because 99.9% SLAs explicitly permit a small amount of downtime.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/support/legal/sla/summary/","label":"Microsoft Azure SLA Summary"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A SaaS company operates a multi-tenant cloud application and has an SLA guaranteeing 99.9% monthly uptime to customers. During a post-incident review, the team calculates that 47 minutes of unplanned downtime occurred last month. Which conclusion is CORRECT?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An operations team wants to implement a monitoring strategy that detects issues BEFORE end users are affected. Which monitoring approach is MOST aligned with this proactive goal?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Reactive monitoring that pages on-call engineers when error rates exceed a defined threshold."},{"id":"b","text":"Synthetic transaction monitoring that continuously simulates user journeys and alerts on failures or latency anomalies."},{"id":"c","text":"Log aggregation with keyword searches triggered by support tickets."},{"id":"d","text":"Real user monitoring (RUM) that captures performance data from actual browser sessions."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Synthetic monitoring uses scripted bots to mimic user transactions at regular intervals, catching degradation before real users encounter it, making it the most proactive option. Reactive threshold alerting (A) responds after a problem is already occurring. Log searches triggered by tickets (C) are purely reactive. RUM (D) captures real user experience data but is inherently reactive—it requires actual users to be affected before generating signals.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://cloud.google.com/monitoring/uptime-checks/introduction","label":"Google Cloud Operations Suite – Synthetic Monitoring"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An operations team wants to implement a monitoring strategy that detects issues BEFORE end users are affected. Which monitoring approach is MOST aligned with this proactive goal?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud administrator is configuring backup policies for a relational database that hosts transactional data. The business requires a Recovery Point Objective (RPO) of 1 hour. Which backup configuration BEST meets this requirement?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Daily full backups stored in geo-redundant object storage."},{"id":"b","text":"Weekly full backups supplemented by daily incremental backups."},{"id":"c","text":"Continuous transaction-log shipping combined with hourly snapshots."},{"id":"d","text":"Daily full backups with a 24-hour retention window."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$An RPO of 1 hour means the business can tolerate losing at most 1 hour of data. Continuous transaction-log shipping captures every committed transaction in near-real-time, while hourly snapshots provide consistent restore points—together ensuring data loss is limited to under 1 hour. Daily full backups alone (A and D) could result in up to 24 hours of data loss. Weekly fulls with daily incrementals (B) could still yield up to 24 hours of loss depending on timing.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonRDS/latest/UserGuide/USER_WorkingWithAutomatedBackups.html","label":"AWS RDS – Automated Backups and Point-in-Time Recovery"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud administrator is configuring backup policies for a relational database that hosts transactional data. The business requires a Recovery Point Objective (RPO) of 1 hour. Which backup configuration BEST meets this requirement?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$During a routine capacity review, an operations analyst notices that a fleet of virtual machines running a batch-processing workload consistently utilizes only 15% of provisioned CPU and memory between midnight and 6 AM daily. Which action BEST optimizes cost while maintaining workload performance?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Migrate the workload to a larger VM size to improve batch completion time."},{"id":"b","text":"Implement a scheduled scaling policy to reduce VM capacity during off-peak hours and restore it before peak processing begins."},{"id":"c","text":"Enable auto-scaling based on CPU utilization with a 90% scale-out threshold."},{"id":"d","text":"Reserve the current VM size for a three-year term to reduce the hourly rate."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Scheduled scaling allows the team to proactively reduce capacity during the predictable off-peak window (midnight–6 AM) and restore it before batch jobs resume, directly eliminating the wasted spend. Upsizing (A) increases cost without addressing underutilization. A CPU-based auto-scaler with a 90% threshold (C) is reactive and would not reduce capacity during known idle periods. Reserving the current oversized configuration for three years (D) locks in the inefficiency at a discounted rate—better than on-demand but still suboptimal compared to right-sizing.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/azure-monitor/autoscale/autoscale-overview","label":"Azure Autoscale with Scheduled Profiles"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$During a routine capacity review, an operations analyst notices that a fleet of virtual machines running a batch-processing workload consistently utilizes only 15% of provisioned CPU and memory between midnight and 6 AM daily. Which action BEST optimizes cost while maintaining workload performance?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud operations team is establishing a runbook-driven incident response process. Which element is MOST critical to include in a runbook to ensure consistent, repeatable resolution of a known incident type?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"A list of all team members' personal contact numbers for escalation."},{"id":"b","text":"Step-by-step remediation procedures with explicit decision points, expected outputs, and escalation criteria."},{"id":"c","text":"A high-level architectural diagram of the entire cloud environment."},{"id":"d","text":"Historical incident ticket data from the past 12 months."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$An effective runbook must give responders unambiguous, ordered steps—including what to check, what output to expect at each step, and when to escalate—so that any qualified operator can execute it consistently under pressure. Personal contact lists (A) belong in an on-call schedule, not a runbook. Architectural diagrams (C) are reference material, not procedural guidance. Historical ticket data (D) informs root-cause analysis but does not provide actionable resolution steps.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://sre.google/workbook/on-call/","label":"Google SRE Workbook – On-Call and Incident Response"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud operations team is establishing a runbook-driven incident response process. Which element is MOST critical to include in a runbook to ensure consistent, repeatable resolution of a known incident type?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud engineer is tasked with reducing the blast radius of a potential misconfiguration during a planned maintenance window that involves updating IAM policies across multiple cloud accounts. Which change-management technique MOST effectively limits risk?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Apply all IAM policy changes simultaneously across every account to minimize the total maintenance window duration."},{"id":"b","text":"Use a canary deployment approach by applying changes to one non-critical account first, validating results, then progressively rolling out to remaining accounts."},{"id":"c","text":"Disable all monitoring alerts during the maintenance window to prevent false-positive pages."},{"id":"d","text":"Back up all IAM policies to a text file on a local workstation before applying changes."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A canary (progressive) rollout limits exposure by applying the change to a small, non-critical scope first. Any unforeseen impact is contained to one account, and findings can be used to abort or adjust before wider rollout—directly minimizing blast radius. Simultaneous deployment (A) maximizes blast radius. Disabling monitoring (C) removes visibility exactly when it is most needed and is a dangerous anti-pattern. Local text-file backups (D) are a poor recovery mechanism compared to version-controlled policy definitions and do not limit risk of a bad change.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/wellarchitected/latest/reliability-pillar/rel_tracking_change_management_planned_changemgmt.html","label":"AWS Deployment Strategies – Canary Deployments"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud engineer is tasked with reducing the blast radius of a potential misconfiguration during a planned maintenance window that involves updating IAM policies across multiple cloud accounts. Which change-management technique MOST effectively limits risk?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An operations team is evaluating log management solutions for a cloud environment that generates approximately 500 GB of log data per day. The compliance requirement mandates that logs be retained and searchable for a minimum of 13 months. Which approach BEST balances cost and compliance?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Store all 13 months of logs in high-performance SSD-backed block storage to ensure fast query times."},{"id":"b","text":"Retain the most recent 30 days of logs in a hot log analytics tier for fast searching, and automatically archive older logs to a low-cost object storage tier with lifecycle policies that enforce 13-month retention."},{"id":"c","text":"Delete logs after 90 days to control storage costs and maintain only summary reports for the compliance period."},{"id":"d","text":"Replicate all logs to an on-premises tape library to avoid cloud storage costs entirely."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A tiered storage strategy stores recent, frequently-queried logs in a hot tier for operational needs while moving older logs to cheap object storage (e.g., S3 Glacier, Azure Archive, GCS Coldline) via lifecycle policies. This satisfies the 13-month retention compliance requirement at a fraction of the cost of keeping everything in hot storage. High-performance block storage for 13 months (A) would be cost-prohibitive at 500 GB/day. Deleting after 90 days (C) violates the 13-month requirement. On-premises tape (D) introduces operational complexity, potential latency for retrieval, and off-cloud risk that typically outweighs savings.$patch$, $patch$Operations and Support$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/userguide/object-lifecycle-mgmt.html","label":"AWS S3 Lifecycle Policies and Storage Classes"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An operations team is evaluating log management solutions for a cloud environment that generates approximately 500 GB of log data per day. The compliance requirement mandates that logs be retained and searchable for a minimum of 13 months. Which approach BEST balances cost and compliance?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud security engineer is designing a multi-tenant SaaS environment and needs to ensure that each tenant's data is logically separated so that one tenant cannot access another tenant's resources. Which cloud security control BEST addresses this requirement?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Implementing network segmentation using Virtual Private Clouds (VPCs) per tenant"},{"id":"b","text":"Enabling multi-factor authentication (MFA) for all tenant administrator accounts"},{"id":"c","text":"Deploying a Web Application Firewall (WAF) in front of the shared application tier"},{"id":"d","text":"Applying data-at-rest encryption using a shared customer-managed key across all tenants"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Creating a dedicated Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) per tenant enforces logical network-level isolation, ensuring that one tenant's traffic, workloads, and data cannot reach another tenant's resources. This is the foundational control for multi-tenancy segmentation in cloud environments. MFA (B) improves authentication security but does not provide data or network isolation between tenants. A WAF (C) protects against web-layer attacks but does not segment tenant data or resources. Using a single shared customer-managed key (D) actually undermines tenant isolation because all tenants would effectively share the same encryption boundary, increasing the risk of cross-tenant data exposure.$patch$, $patch$Security$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives – Security Domain"},{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-204/final","label":"NIST SP 800-204 – Security Strategies for Microservices-based Application Systems (Multi-tenancy isolation)"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud security engineer is designing a multi-tenant SaaS environment and needs to ensure that each tenant's data is logically separated so that one tenant cannot access another tenant's resources. Which cloud security control BEST addresses this requirement?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$During a security audit, a cloud administrator discovers that several IAM service accounts have been granted the built-in Owner role at the organization level in their cloud environment. The auditor flags this as a critical finding. Which security principle has been violated, and what remediation action should be taken FIRST?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Violation of separation of duties; rotate the service account keys immediately"},{"id":"b","text":"Violation of least privilege; replace the Owner role with narrowly scoped custom roles granting only the permissions each service account requires"},{"id":"c","text":"Violation of defense in depth; enable cloud audit logging to capture all API calls made by the service accounts"},{"id":"d","text":"Violation of non-repudiation; enforce MFA on all service accounts and store credentials in a secrets manager"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Granting the Owner role at the organization level to service accounts violates the principle of least privilege, which requires that identities be given only the minimum permissions necessary to perform their intended function. The correct first remediation step is to replace the overly broad Owner role with custom or predefined roles that are scoped to the specific actions each service account must perform, and to limit the resource scope to only the projects or resources needed. Rotating keys (A) addresses credential hygiene but does not fix the excessive-permissions problem. Enabling audit logging (C) is a good detective control but does not reduce the attack surface. Enforcing MFA on service accounts (D) is generally not applicable to non-human service accounts and does not resolve the privilege violation.$patch$, $patch$Security$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives – Security Domain"},{"url":"https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/using-iam-securely#least_privilege","label":"Google Cloud – IAM best practices: Principle of least privilege"},{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/publications/detail/sp/800-53/rev-5/final","label":"NIST SP 800-53 Rev 5 – AC-6: Least Privilege"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$During a security audit, a cloud administrator discovers that several IAM service accounts have been granted the built-in Owner role at the organization level in their cloud environment. The auditor flags this as a critical finding. Which security principle has been violated, and what remediation action should be taken FIRST?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A company stores sensitive customer records in an object storage bucket. A security review reveals that the bucket is inadvertently publicly accessible. After immediately restricting public access, the security team wants to implement a control that will automatically detect and alert on any future public-exposure misconfigurations across ALL storage resources in the cloud account. Which solution BEST fulfills this requirement?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Enable server-side encryption with customer-managed keys (SSE-CMK) on all storage buckets"},{"id":"b","text":"Configure a Cloud Security Posture Management (CSPM) tool to continuously evaluate storage resource configurations against a security baseline and generate alerts for public-access policy violations"},{"id":"c","text":"Deploy a host-based intrusion detection system (HIDS) on the virtual machines that access the storage buckets"},{"id":"d","text":"Implement a VPN gateway to ensure all client connections to storage resources are tunneled through the corporate network"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Cloud Security Posture Management (CSPM) tool continuously monitors cloud resource configurations, compares them against security benchmarks and policies, and generates real-time alerts when misconfigurations (such as publicly exposed storage buckets) are detected. This is the most direct control for proactively identifying and alerting on configuration drift across all storage resources in the account. SSE-CMK (A) protects data confidentiality at rest but does nothing to detect or prevent misconfigured access policies. A HIDS (C) monitors activity on individual compute instances and cannot evaluate the configuration state of storage services. A VPN gateway (D) secures network transport but does not prevent an administrator from accidentally setting a bucket policy to public, nor does it alert on such misconfigurations.$patch$, $patch$Security$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives – Security Domain"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/securityhub/latest/userguide/what-is-securityhub.html","label":"AWS – What is AWS Security Hub? (CSPM capabilities)"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/defender-for-cloud/defender-for-cloud-introduction","label":"Microsoft Learn – What is Microsoft Defender for Cloud? (CSPM overview)"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A company stores sensitive customer records in an object storage bucket. A security review reveals that the bucket is inadvertently publicly accessible. After immediately restricting public access, the security team wants to implement a control that will automatically detect and alert on any future public-exposure misconfigurations across ALL storage resources in the cloud account. Which solution BEST fulfills this requirement?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud administrator receives alerts that a multi-tier web application hosted on a public cloud provider is experiencing intermittent 504 Gateway Timeout errors. The application consists of a load balancer, web tier, application tier, and a managed relational database. CPU and memory utilization across all tiers appear normal. Which component should the administrator investigate FIRST to isolate the root cause?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The load balancer's idle connection timeout and request timeout settings"},{"id":"b","text":"The virtual machine disk I/O throughput on the web tier"},{"id":"c","text":"The TLS certificate expiration date on the load balancer"},{"id":"d","text":"The auto-scaling cooldown period for the web tier"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A 504 Gateway Timeout means the upstream server (application tier) did not respond to the load balancer within the configured timeout window. When CPU and memory are normal, the most likely culprit is a mismatch between the load balancer's timeout settings and the time the application tier needs to complete a request. Investigating and aligning these timeout values is the first logical step. Disk I/O (b) would typically surface as high latency metrics, not clean timeouts. TLS expiration (c) would produce 502 or SSL handshake errors, not 504s. Auto-scaling cooldown (d) would manifest as capacity exhaustion reflected in high CPU/memory, which was ruled out.$patch$, $patch$Troubleshooting$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ CV0-004 Exam Objectives"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/elasticloadbalancing/latest/application/load-balancer-troubleshooting.html#http-504-issues","label":"AWS – Troubleshoot HTTP 504 errors from your load balancer"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud administrator receives alerts that a multi-tier web application hosted on a public cloud provider is experiencing intermittent 504 Gateway Timeout errors. The application consists of a load balancer, web tier, application tier, and a managed relational database. CPU and memory utilization across all tiers appear normal. Which component should the administrator investigate FIRST to isolate the root cause?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Users in a remote branch office report that latency to a cloud-hosted SaaS application has increased dramatically over the past 48 hours. No changes were made to the application itself. A network engineer reviews flow logs and finds that traffic is being routed through a distant regional hub rather than the nearest cloud edge location. What is the MOST likely root cause?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The SaaS application's SLA has been downgraded by the vendor"},{"id":"b","text":"A BGP route change or misconfiguration is directing traffic suboptimally"},{"id":"c","text":"The branch office firewall is performing deep packet inspection on HTTPS traffic"},{"id":"d","text":"The cloud provider's CDN cache has been purged and is being repopulated"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$When traffic suddenly takes a longer path through a distant hub rather than the nearest edge, a BGP route advertisement change or misconfiguration is the primary suspect. BGP path selection can change due to route withdrawals, changed MED/AS-path attributes, or ISP peering changes, none of which require application-level changes. SLA downgrade (a) would not alter routing paths. Deep packet inspection (c) adds latency uniformly but does not reroute traffic to a different geographic hub. CDN cache purges (d) affect content delivery for cacheable objects, not the routing path of application traffic.$patch$, $patch$Troubleshooting$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/cloud","label":"CompTIA Cloud+ Study Guide – Network Troubleshooting"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/directconnect/latest/UserGuide/routing-and-bgp.html","label":"AWS – BGP Best Practices for AWS Direct Connect"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$Users in a remote branch office report that latency to a cloud-hosted SaaS application has increased dramatically over the past 48 hours. No changes were made to the application itself. A network engineer reviews flow logs and finds that traffic is being routed through a distant regional hub rather than the nearest cloud edge location. What is the MOST likely root cause?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A DevOps team deploys a containerized microservice to a Kubernetes cluster. The pods start successfully but the service is unreachable from other pods within the same namespace. The team confirms the pods are in Running state and the correct container port is exposed. Which of the following is the MOST likely cause of the connectivity failure?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The container image was pulled from an untrusted registry"},{"id":"b","text":"The Kubernetes Service object's selector labels do not match the pod labels"},{"id":"c","text":"The node's kubelet service has crashed and needs to be restarted"},{"id":"d","text":"The persistent volume claim attached to the pod is in a Pending state"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$A Kubernetes Service routes traffic to pods by matching its selector labels against pod labels. If there is a label mismatch, the Service will have no Endpoints, and traffic will never reach the pods even though they are Running. An untrusted registry (a) would cause an ImagePullBackOff error, not a running pod. A crashed kubelet (c) would prevent pods from being scheduled or maintained in Running state. A PVC in Pending state (d) would block the pod from starting at all, not cause network unreachability for an already-running pod.$patch$, $patch$Troubleshooting$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug/debug-application/debug-service/","label":"Kubernetes – Debugging Services"},{"url":"https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/service/#selector","label":"Kubernetes – Service selectors"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A DevOps team deploys a containerized microservice to a Kubernetes cluster. The pods start successfully but the service is unreachable from other pods within the same namespace. The team confirms the pods are in Running state and the correct container port is exposed. Which of the following is the MOST likely cause of the connectivity failure?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An operations team notices that nightly batch jobs running on cloud virtual machines are completing successfully but taking 40% longer than the established baseline. The jobs are I/O-intensive and read large data sets from attached block storage. CPU utilization remains low. Which troubleshooting step should be performed FIRST?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Increase the number of vCPUs assigned to the virtual machines"},{"id":"b","text":"Review block storage throughput and IOPS metrics to determine if the volume is being throttled"},{"id":"c","text":"Migrate the workload to a serverless compute platform to eliminate the overhead"},{"id":"d","text":"Re-deploy the virtual machines in a different availability zone"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$When I/O-intensive jobs slow down while CPU remains low, the bottleneck is almost certainly in storage throughput or IOPS. Cloud block storage volumes have defined IOPS and bandwidth ceilings, and exceeding the provisioned limits causes throttling, which manifests exactly as increased job duration without elevated CPU. Reviewing storage metrics is the correct first step. Adding vCPUs (a) would not help an I/O-bound workload. Migrating to serverless (c) is a major architectural change that bypasses root-cause analysis. Changing availability zones (d) does not alter storage performance characteristics.$patch$, $patch$Troubleshooting$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ebs/latest/userguide/ebs-volume-types.html","label":"AWS – Amazon EBS volume performance"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-machines/disks-performance","label":"Azure – Virtual machine disk performance"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An operations team notices that nightly batch jobs running on cloud virtual machines are completing successfully but taking 40% longer than the established baseline. The jobs are I/O-intensive and read large data sets from attached block storage. CPU utilization remains low. Which troubleshooting step should be performed FIRST?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$After a routine maintenance window, an infrastructure engineer discovers that an application server can no longer reach its backend database server, even though both resources are in the same virtual private cloud. The database was previously reachable. No application code was changed. Which of the following changes made during maintenance is the MOST likely cause?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The database server's OS was patched and rebooted, changing its private IP address via DHCP"},{"id":"b","text":"The inbound security group rule permitting the application server's IP to connect on the database port was removed"},{"id":"c","text":"The application server's auto-scaling group minimum instance count was reduced to zero"},{"id":"d","text":"The cloud provider's managed database service was upgraded to a newer engine version"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$Security groups act as stateful virtual firewalls. If the inbound rule allowing the application server's traffic on the database port (e.g., 3306 for MySQL, 5432 for PostgreSQL) was accidentally removed during maintenance, all connection attempts will be silently dropped, causing the exact symptom described. Cloud-managed instances typically retain static private IPs or use DNS endpoints, so a DHCP IP change (a) is unlikely and would cause wider issues. If the auto-scaling group minimum were set to zero (c), the application server itself would terminate, not just lose database access. A database engine upgrade (d) might cause temporary downtime or compatibility issues but would not persistently block connectivity unless accompanied by a security group change.$patch$, $patch$Troubleshooting$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/vpc-security-groups.html","label":"AWS – Security groups for your VPC"},{"url":"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-network/network-security-groups-overview","label":"Azure – Network security groups overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$After a routine maintenance window, an infrastructure engineer discovers that an application server can no longer reach its backend database server, even though both resources are in the same virtual private cloud. The database was previously reachable. No application code was changed. Which of the following changes made during maintenance is the MOST likely cause?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud engineer is investigating why a newly deployed serverless function is failing with a timeout error during execution. The function processes messages from a queue and writes results to object storage. Logs show the function initializes correctly and begins processing, but never completes. The function's timeout is set to 30 seconds and memory is adequate. Which configuration item should the engineer examine FIRST?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Whether the function's execution role has the required permissions to write to the object storage bucket"},{"id":"b","text":"Whether the object storage bucket's versioning feature is enabled"},{"id":"c","text":"Whether the queue's message retention period has been exceeded"},{"id":"d","text":"Whether the function runtime version has reached end-of-life"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$When a serverless function initializes and begins processing but hangs until timeout, an authorization failure on a downstream API call (such as writing to object storage) is a very common cause. Without the necessary IAM/execution role permissions, the write request will either be blocked or hang while the SDK retries, eventually exhausting the function's timeout without returning an error visible in the main log stream. Bucket versioning (b) does not affect write permissions or cause timeouts. Message retention (c) affects whether messages are available to consume, not execution duration once processing has started. An end-of-life runtime (d) might produce deprecation warnings but would not cause intermittent hangs mid-execution.$patch$, $patch$Troubleshooting$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-intro-execution-role.html","label":"AWS – Lambda execution role"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/troubleshooting-execution.html","label":"AWS – Troubleshooting Lambda"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud engineer is investigating why a newly deployed serverless function is failing with a timeout error during execution. The function processes messages from a queue and writes results to object storage. Logs show the function initializes correctly and begins processing, but never completes. The function's timeout is set to 30 seconds and memory is adequate. Which configuration item should the engineer examine FIRST?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A cloud administrator receives reports that virtual machines in a production environment are being automatically terminated and replaced without any administrator action. The environment uses auto-scaling groups and a health-check integration with the application load balancer. The replacement instances pass initial launch checks but are terminated shortly after. Which of the following is the MOST likely root cause?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The load balancer's health check path is returning a non-2xx HTTP status code, causing instances to be marked unhealthy"},{"id":"b","text":"The auto-scaling group's desired capacity setting has been set lower than the minimum capacity"},{"id":"c","text":"The instances are failing AWS Systems Manager patch compliance checks"},{"id":"d","text":"The cloud provider's spot instance interruption notices are terminating the instances"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$When auto-scaling continuously terminates and replaces instances that appear healthy at launch, the most probable cause is that the load balancer health check is failing after the instance registers. If the health check endpoint returns a 4xx or 5xx status—due to a misconfigured path, a missing application process, or a dependency outage—the load balancer marks the instance unhealthy, the auto-scaling group detects the failed health check, terminates the instance, and launches a replacement that suffers the same fate, creating a replacement loop. A desired capacity lower than minimum (b) would produce a configuration validation error, not a termination loop. SSM patch compliance (c) does not trigger auto-scaling termination actions by default. Spot interruptions (d) are possible but would be visible in interruption notices and would not cause a steady replace-and-terminate cycle unless all instances were spot and demand were continuously high.$patch$, $patch$Troubleshooting$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/ec2-auto-scaling-health-checks.html","label":"AWS – Health checks for Auto Scaling instances"},{"url":"https://docs.aws.amazon.com/autoscaling/ec2/userguide/CHAP_Troubleshooting.html","label":"AWS – Troubleshoot Auto Scaling"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = 'CV0-004-P8'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A cloud administrator receives reports that virtual machines in a production environment are being automatically terminated and replaced without any administrator action. The environment uses auto-scaling groups and a health-check integration with the application load balancer. The replacement instances pass initial launch checks but are terminated shortly after. Which of the following is the MOST likely root cause?$patch$);

